pageContext.claim: “If their agenda kept going forward, meaning if the other side had won, we would have been down 4.2, or six or seven -- we were going down. It was very bad when I took it over. And if we didn't open it up and cut regulations, the whole Obama thing would have collapsed it. It would have been a disaster.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump inherited a growing economy from Obama and there is no evidence the economy would have plunged if Clinton had been elected.
